<br>
Keep the Rogue Redeemption quest in the game and maybe increase the stats slightly to put it more on par with some of the other mid-level rogue piercers in the game to keep more Rogues using it.  Maybe stats similar to Slime Coated (just throwin out an example).<br>
<br>
Here's my dream Epic Weapon II<br>
<br>
I'd say keep the Ragebringer (RB) the way it is or just a slight modification to &quot;bring it in line with high end weapons&quot; as VI puts it.  How about like other dual wielders, give us a 2nd epic weapon (like rangers and warriors).  The RB will remain and be used.  <br>
<br>
The new piercer will be obtained in a quest to upgrade the BR.  Give us quests to obtain specific components needed to upgrade the BR.  The quest could parallel or even oppose the RB quest with revisits to some of the scenes in the RB quest.   The quest should include the necessity of the use of our particular talents, poison making, lockpicking, sneaking into hostile territory and pickpocketing, sneaking into hostile territory, etc.  A certain number of components are quested/side-quested for and turned in to a NPC along with the BR and voila.... we receive our 2nd Epic Weapon.  <br>
<br>
It could be called The Rapier Of The Assassin (ROA) and be an upgraded BR with a new graphic.  In a dual-wield setup, the RB would again be favored as a main hand and the ROA would be designed to compliment the RB or whatever you choose as Primary.  <br>
<br>
The ROA would have some type of proc or click effect that is in-line with our class.  I have a couple ideas on the type of proc or effect.<br>
<br>
1.  Have a proc or effect to reduce or wipe agro.  Maybe have the effect similar the the Evade that is one of our advanced skills.  My thoughts are you hit a wicked double backstab and draw agro, the proc/click effect on the ROA would immediately wipe our agro.  Another interesting effect would be Feign Death (that'll piss the monk community off).  If you draw unwanted agro, you can click your epic and FD.  <br>
<br>
2.  I personally detest the poison skill and gave up on it along time ago.  How about making the ROA have a poison proc that is equal to our best poisons?  <br>
<br>
Just some thoughts and ideas. Having either option would really appeal to me.  I don't know where to post these types of ideas to Verant, so maybe someone can pass this along.  I don't mind questing and camping as long as the end result is worth it and will fit in to what we do in the end game.  <br>
<br>
I have way too much time on my hands.<br>
<br>
Nobbil SpineSplitter<br>
57th Level Dragon Butt-Poker<br>
Proud Member of Lords Of The Dragon<br>
